prompt: Generate Cisco IOS XR 7.0.1 telemetry model-driven configuration for platform inventory + hardware state (FRU inventory entities + operational status). Use gRPC with no TLS. Server 192.0.2.124 port 57500. Use a 2-minute sample interval.
candidate:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group PLATFORM-INVENTORY
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/subscriptions/subscription
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/subscriptions/subscription/subscription/source-interface
 !
 destination-group DG-GRPC
  address-family ipv4
   destination 192.0.2.124
    port 57500
    encoding self-describing-gpb
    protocol grpc no-tls
 !
 subscription PLATFORM-STATE
  sensor-group-id PLATFORM-INVENTORY sample-interval 120000
  destination-group-id DG-GRPC
 !
rationale: The candidate config uses the correct IP (192.0.2.124), port (57500), transport (grpc no-tls), and encoding (self-describing-gpb), which meets the hard requirements. However, the sensor-paths are unrelated to the requested platform inventory and hardware state (FRU inventory entities + operational status). The candidate's sensor-paths refer to telemetry-model-driven subscriptions and interfaces, not the expected inventory and platform operational data. Naming and sample-interval are acceptable but irrelevant due to incorrect sensor-paths.
